											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">&nbsp;</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="307">
												<P>Dual wield. Increases the chance for the bard to successfully attack with both equipped weapons during a round of combat.</P>
											</TD>
										</TR>
										<TR>
											<TD width="12">
												<P align="center">59</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="61">
												<P align="center">Instrument Mastery</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="27">
												<P align="center">3/6/9</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="25">
												<P align="center">3</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">0.2/ 0.4/ 0.6</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="307">
												<P>Increases the modifier for instrument-based songs. Stacks with all other modifiers including instruments, epic, and Puretone. This is a passive ability so the modifier is always added. The 1st Level adds a 0.2 modifier, the 2nd adds 0.4, and the third adds a modifier of 0.6.</P>
											</TD>
										</TR>
										<TR>
											<TD width="12">
												<P align="center">59</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="61">
												<P align="center">Jam Fest</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="27">
												<P align="center">3/6/9</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="25">
												<P align="center">3</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">1 effective level per AA level</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="307">
												<P>Increases the effective level of the bard when level is taken into account on certain songs. Songs which factor in player level include damage songs, charms, and mez. This ability does not allow bards to memorize songs above their actual level.</P>
											</TD>
										</TR>
										<TR>
											<TD width="12">
												<P align="center">59</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="61">
												<P align="center">Extended Notes</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="27">
												<P align="center">3/6/9</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="25">
												<P align="center">3</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">10%/15%/25%</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="307">
												<P>Increases the range of bard group songs, meaning that fellow members of the bard’s group can be farther away and still receive the benefit of the song. It does not increase the radius for AoE songs.</P>
											</TD>
										</TR>
										<TR>
											<TD width="12">
												<P align="center">59</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="61">
												<P align="center">Singing Mastery</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="27">
												<P align="center">3/6/9</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="25">
												<P align="center">3</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">0.2/ 0.4/ 0.6</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="307">
												<P>Adds a modifier to singing-based songs. Stacks with all other modifiers including epic, Amp, Puretone, Harmonize, and Resonance. This is a passive ability so the modifier is always added. The 1st Level adds a 0.2 modifier, the 2nd adds 0.4, and the third adds a modifier of 0.6.</P>
											</TD>
										</TR>
										<TR>
											<TD width="12">
												<P align="center">59</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="61">
												<P align="center">Body and Mind Rejuvenation</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="27">
												<P align="center">5</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="25">
												<P align="center">1</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">1 HP &amp; 1 mana/tick per AA level</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="307">
												<P>Adds an additional level to both Natural Healing and Mental Clarity, further increasing mana and HP regeneration per tick. Prerequisites: Natural Healing 3 &amp; Mental Clarity 3</P>
											</TD>
										</TR>
										<TR>
											<TD width="12">
												<P align="center">59</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="61">
												<P align="center">Physical Enhancement</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="27">
												<P align="center">5</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="25">
												<P align="center">1</P>
											</TD>
											<TD width="2">
												<P align="center">2%</P>
											</TD>
